Direct axis stator current - Produces reluctance torque in conjunction with quadrature axis currents. Negative in order to produce any positive torque (when ld is smaller than lq) a positive id is never desired.
Quadrature axis stator current - Produces only magnetic torque but do not contribute in producing reluctance torque
Inductance along Direct axis - Inductance along the d-axis is usually lower than that along the q-axis (ld is smaller than lq)
Inductance along Quadrature axis - Permanent magnets have higher reluctance than iron (lq is greater than ld)
Voltage along Direct axis
Voltage along Quadrature axis
